summary: PURCHASED A NEW PONTIAC GTO, CAR WAS BUILT IN FEBRUARY OF 2006, TOOK DELIVERY IN LATE MAY.  AFTER ~3100 MILES OF NORMAL DRIVING, A POPPING SOUND STARTED COMING FROM THE FRONT PASSENGER SIDE.  THE SOUND WAS CAUSED BY A FAILING MACPHERSON STRUT THAT HAS BEEN REPORTED ON OTHER GTO'S BUILT IN FEBRUARY 2006.  *NM
